    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Nov. 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am much obliged to you for your great kindness in having sent me your work “Die Welt &amp;c”, which I hope soon to read, but I am to my great grief a very poor German scholar &amp; a book in that language takes me a very long time.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>With much respect, Dear Sir | Yours faithfully &amp; obliged | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is conjectured from the reference to Noiré’s book (see n. 2, below), which was published in 1874.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD’s copy of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5896.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Noiré 1874</ref>, <hi rend="italic">Die Welt als Entwicklung des Geistes. Bausteine zu einer monistischen Weltanschauung</hi> (The world as development of the intellect: the elements of a monistic worldview), is in the Darwin Library–Down.</note>
        </div>        
            
